# Linux Security Baseline Audit Checklist

## User & Access Review
- List all local users
- Identify users with sudo privileges
- Check for inactive or unnecessary accounts

## File & Permission Review
- Identify world-writable files
- Review permissions on sensitive directories
- Check ownership of system files

## Service Review
- List running services
- Identify unnecessary or unused services
- Review services listening on network ports

## Logging & Monitoring
- Verify log files exist
- Check basic log permissions
- Confirm logs are being written

## Observations
- Document potential risks
- Provide basic recommendations
